{
  "stem": "1917.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 290.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And then the train moved again in the next stop.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "It was still dark.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "My father asked for water.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Nobody even answered.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But you could hear a lot of footsteps outside running back and forth, Germans yelling orders.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "That went on probably for about an hour.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We couldn't see anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "There was dark.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And-- and my father gathered us in the corner of the cattle car and said, children, I don't know what's happening, where we are.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "But if any of you survive this terrible war, please make sure that you're going to go to Palestine, because I believe that you have an uncle there by the name of Aaron.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And I believe the Jews can live there in peace and freedom.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And we promised.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "With tears in our eyes, we promised.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "I realized my father never even spoke to us as grown ups before.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I-- he opened his prayer book like nothing happened-- tried to figure out the direction-- which direction was east, and began his morning prayers with his [NON-ENGLISH] and his tallit, and everything, in the midst of crying and screaming children.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And many other Jews joining in were praying to God probably for the last time to help them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "I was angry.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "It looked so hopeless.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "It-- you could-- we knew we were in Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "We didn't know where.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Finally, the cattle car door slid open and this mass of people poured out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "We stepped down.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "My mother grabbed my sister and me by the  hand.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was trying to look around to see where on earth-- where we-- what is that place?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What does it look like?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everything looked gray, lifeless, huge barbed wires, the smell.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And suddenly, I realized that my father and my two older sisters disappeared in the crowd.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
